{"title_page": "Manoj Sarkar", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name = Manoj Sarkar\n| image = [[File:The President, Shri Ram Nath Kovind presenting the Arjuna Award, 2018 to Shri Manoj Sarkar for Para-Badminton, in a glittering ceremony, at Rashtrapati Bhavan, in New Delhi on September 25, 2018.JPG|thumb|Manoj Sarkar]]\n| birth_name = Manoj Sarkar <ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/player-profile/2fa10d67-7dd2-48e4-a099-8be02fd5503c/biography</ref>\n| fullname = \n| nickname = \n| nationality = {{IND}}\n| residence =  \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|01|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Rudrapur]],[[Uttrakhand]] India\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| weight = \n| website = \n| country = {{IND}}\n| sport = [[Badminton]] \n| event = [[Singles]]\n| disability = PPRP Lower Limb condition\n| disability_class = SL-3\n| club = \n| team = \n| turnedpro = \n| coach = \n| retired = \n| coaching = \n| worlds = \n| regionals = \n| nationals = \n| olympics = \n| paralympics = \n| highestranking = (Men's Singles SL3 - 1) (Men's Doubles SL3-SL4 - 1)\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[Para-badminton]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{IND}} }}\n\n{{MedalCompetition|[[2019 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]}}<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/player.aspx?id=645DCFB9-4DEF-44A5-8CFB-4B2C38B03294&player=98</ref>\n{{MedalBronze|[[Basel, Switzerland]]|Men's Singles SL3}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Basel, Switzerland]]|Men's Doubles SL3-SL4}}\n\n{{MedalCompetition|[[2018 Asian Para Games]]}}<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/player.aspx?id=62CF57E0-E40B-42D8-B04B-4A4891183AA5&player=16</ref>\n{{MedalBronze|[[Jakarta, Indonesia]]|Men's Singles SL3}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Jakarta, Indonesia]]|Men's Doubles SL3-SL4}}\n\n{{MedalCompetition|BWF Para-Badminton World Championships 2017}}<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/player.aspx?id=02949A40-0043-4A81-AAA7-CCDC38219288&player=183</ref>\n{{MedalSilver|[[Ulsan, South Korea]]|Men's Singles SL3}}\n\n{{MedalCompetition|Asian Para-Badminton Championships 2016}}<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/player.aspx?id=C88ED65D-5F60-4652-B853-C72E8CE34C0F&player=54</ref>\n{{MedalGold|[[Beijing]]|Men's Singles SL3}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Beijing]]|Men's Doubles SL3-SL4}}\n\n{{MedalCompetition|[[2015 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]}}<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/player.aspx?id=373F4ADE-ED29-4899-8266-474278A4F9C3&player=175</ref>\n{{MedalBronze|[[Stoke Mandeville, England]]|Men's Singles SL3}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Stoke Mandeville, England]]|Men's Doubles SL3-SL4}}\n\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n\n'''Manoj Sarkar''' is the current World no.1 [[Para-badminton]] player in the SL-3 Classification.<ref>https://bwfpara.tournamentsoftware.com/player-profile/2fa10d67-7dd2-48e4-a099-8be02fd5503c/biography</ref> He has won a Silver medal in the BWF Para-Badminton World championships, 2017 in the Singles event. He is supported by the [[GoSports Foundation]] through the Para Champions Programme.\n\n== Early life and background ==\n\nManoj\u2019s condition arose out of wrongful medical treatment at the age of 1. Ha hails from amodest background and has 2 siblings. He suffers from a PPRP Lower Limb condition.\n\n== Career ==\n\nManoj has won numerous accolades in the International circuit including a Men's Singles Silver at the Thailand Para-Badminton International 2017, A Gold at the Uganda Para-Badminton International 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=58EB12CC-845E-40B5-85AD-AD5C6F2E2295|title=BWF - Uganda Para-Badminton International 2017 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>, A silver at the Irish Para-Badminton International 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=2A04AE2A-1B9D-4BC6-8932-605F7B860186|title=BWF - Irish Para-Badminton International 2016 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref> and a Gold in the Men's Doubes event at the BWF Para-Badminton World Championships 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=373F4ADE-ED29-4899-8266-474278A4F9C3|title=BWF - BWF Para-Badminton World Championships 2015 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>\n\n== Achievements ==\n''[[BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n! Year\n! Venue\n! Event\n! Score\n! Result\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#FFE4B5\"\n| align=\"center\" | 2019\n| align=\"left\" | [[2019 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[Men's Singles SL3]]\n| align=\"left\" | \n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" |  '''Bronze'''\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#FFE4B5\"\n| align=\"center\" | 2019\n| align=\"left\" | [[2019 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[Men's Doubles SL3-SL4]]\n| align=\"left\" |\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" |  '''Gold'''\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#FFE4B5\"\n| align=\"center\" | 2017\n| align=\"left\" | [[2017 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[Men's Singles SL3]]\n| align=\"left\" | 15-21 21-19 21-16\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" |  '''Silver'''\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#FFE4B5\"\n| align=\"center\" | 2015\n| align=\"left\" | [[2015 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[Men's Singles SL3]]\n| align=\"left\" | \n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" |  '''Bronze'''\n|-\n|-style=\"background:#FFE4B5\"\n| align=\"center\" | 2015\n| align=\"left\" | [[2015 BWF Para-Badminton World Championships]]\n| align=\"left\" | [[Men's Doubles SL3-SL4]]\n| align=\"left\" | 7-21 21-14 21-6\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" |  '''Gold'''\n|}\n\n\n''[[2018 Asian Para Games]]''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n! Year\n! Venue\n! Event\n! Score\n! Result\n|-