9AC02B6C-876C-4BA9-ACBF-93483E291A02|title=BWF - 4th Turkish Para-Badminton International - ENESCUP 2018 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>\n{{MedalGold|[[Konya, Turkey]]|Singles}}\n{{MedalCompetition|1st Fazza - Dubai Para-Badminton International 2018}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=8A06F86B-6B62-42B4-A884-62D309902DBC|title=BWF - 1st Fazza - Dubai Para-Badminton International 2018 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>\n{{MedalGold|[[Dubai]]|Singles}}\n{{MedalCompetition|BWF Para-Badminton World Championships 2017}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=02949A40-0043-4A81-AAA7-CCDC38219288|title=BWF - BWF Para-Badminton World Championships 2017 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>\n{{MedalSilver|[[Ulsan]]|Singles}}\n{{MedalCompetition|Asian Para-Badminton Championships 2016}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bwf.tournamentsoftware.com/sport/winners.aspx?id=C88ED65D-5F60-4652-B853-C72E8CE34C0F|title=BWF - Asian Para-Badminton Championships 2016 - Winners|website=bwf.tournamentsoftware.com}}</ref>\n{{MedalGold|[[Beijing]]|Singles}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[Beijing]]|Doubles}}\n| show-medals = yes\n}}\n\n'''Manoj Sarkar''' is the current World no.1 [[Para-badminton]] player in the SL-3 Classification<ref name=\"bwf.website\"/>. He has won a Silver medal in the BWF Para-Badminton World championships, 2017 in the Singles event. He is supported by the [[GoSports Foundation]] through the Para Champions Programme.\n\n== Early life and background ==\n\nManoj\u2019s condition arose out of wrongful medical treatment at the age of 1. Ha hails from amodest background and has 2 siblings. He suffers from a PPRP Lower Limb condition.\n\n== Career ==\n\nManoj has won numerous accolades in the International circuit including a Men's Singles Silver at the Thailand Para-Badminton International 2017, A Gold at the Uganda Para-Badminton International 2017<ref>{{cite web|ur